69
00:12:23.601 --> 00:12:28.500
But but with the virtues that are our legacy is a free people.

70
00:12:29.101 --> 00:12:38.200
And with a vigilance that sustains liberty, we still have time to use our renewed compact to overcome the injuries that have been done to America these past 3 1/2 years.

71
00:12:38.901 --> 00:12:41.300
First, we must overcome something.

72
00:12:41.301 --> 00:12:47.800
The present administration has cooked up a new and altogether indigestible economic Stew.

73
00:12:48.601 --> 00:13:01.600
One part inflation, one part high unemployment, one part recession, one part runaway taxes, one part deficit spending seasoned with an energy crisis.

74
00:13:01.901 --> 00:13:05.300
It's an economic Stew that has turned the national stomach.

75
00:13:17.801 --> 00:13:21.200
Ours are not problems of abstract economic theory.

76
00:13:22.301 --> 00:13:35.600
These are problems of flesh and blood, problems that cause pain and destroy the moral fiber of real people who should not suffer the further indignity of being told by the government that it is all somehow their fault.

77
00:13:36.601 --> 00:13:38.900
We do not have inflation because, as Mr.

78
00:13:38.901 --> 00:13:40.800
Carter says, we've lived too well.

79
00:13:41.601 --> 00:14:00.000
The head of a government which has utterly refused to live within its means, and which has in the last few days told us that this coming year's deficit will be $60 billion, dares to point the finger of blame at business and labour, both of which have been engaged in a losing struggle just trying to stay.

80
00:14:00.001 --> 00:14:20.400
Even high taxes, we are told, are somehow good for us, as if when government spends our money, it isn't inflationary, but when we spend it, it is.

81
00:14:23.401 --> 00:14:37.600
Those, those who preside over the worst energy shortage in our history tell us to use less, so that we will run out of oil, gasoline and natural gas a little more slowly.

82
00:14:38.401 --> 00:14:44.600
Well, now, conservation is desirable, of course, but we we mustn't waste energy.

83
00:14:45.001 --> 00:14:49.900
But conservation is not the sole answer to our energy needs.

84
00:14:50.501 --> 00:14:53.900
America must get to work producing more energy.

85
00:15:03.901 --> 00:15:10.300
The Republican program for solving economic problems is based on growth and productivity.

86
00:15:11.001 --> 00:15:26.600
Large amounts of oil and natural gas lay beneath our land and off our shores, untouched, because the present administration seems to believe the American people would rather see more regulation, more taxes, and more controls than more energy.

87
00:15:27.601 --> 00:15:29.300
Coal offers a great potential.

88
00:15:29.701 --> 00:15:31.100
So does nuclear energy.

89
00:15:31.101 --> 00:15:47.800
Produced under rigorous safety standards, it could supply electricity for thousands of industry and millions of jobs and homes.

90
00:15:48.201 --> 00:15:58.900
It must not be thwarted by a tiny minority opposed to economic growth, which often finds friendly ears in regulatory agencies for its obstructionist campaigns.

91
00:16:06.101 --> 00:16:15.600
Now, make no mistake, we will not permit the safety of our people or our environmental heritage to be jeopardized.

92
00:16:16.201 --> 00:16:25.300
But we are going to reaffirm that the economic prosperity of our people is a fundamental part of our environment.

93
00:16:32.501 --> 00:16:33.600
Our problems.

94
00:16:34.401 --> 00:16:36.600
Our problems are both acute and chronic.

95
00:16:37.301 --> 00:16:48.200
Yet all we hear from those in positions of leadership are the same tired proposals for more government tinkering, more meddling and more control, all of which led us to this sorry state in the 1st place.

96
00:16:48.801 --> 00:16:52.800
Can anyone look at the record of this administration and say well done?

97
00:16:56.301 --> 00:17:04.099
Can anyone compare the state of our economy when the Carter administration took office with where we are today and say keep up the good work?

98
00:17:07.001 --> 00:17:13.500
Can anyone look at our reduced standing in the world today and say, let's have four more years of this?

99
00:17:16.600 --> 00:17:25.599
I believe the American people are going to answer these questions as you've answered them in the first week in November and their answer will be no, we've had enough.

100
00:17:33.101 --> 00:17:49.600
And then, and then it will be up to us, beginning next January 20th, to offer an administration and congressional leadership of competence and more than a little courage.

101
00:17:50.401 --> 00:17:57.400
We must have the clarity of vision to see the difference between what is essential and what is merely desirable.

102
00:17:58.001 --> 00:18:02.700
And then the courage to bring our government back under control.

103
00:18:03.601 --> 00:18:03.900
It is.

104
00:18:03.901 --> 00:18:06.200
It is essential.

105
00:18:10.301 --> 00:18:20.400
It is essential that we maintain both the forward momentum of economic growth and the strength of the safety net between those in our society who need help.

106
00:18:21.301 --> 00:18:42.200
We also believe it is essential that the integrity of all aspects of Social Security be preserved beyond, Beyond these essentials, I believe it is clear our federal government is overgrown and overweight.

107
00:18:42.801 --> 00:18:46.300
Indeed, it is time our government should go on a diet.

108
00:18:56.801 --> 00:19:06.400
Therefore, my first act as chief executive will be to impose an immediate and thorough freeze on federal hiring.

109
00:19:18.201 --> 00:19:34.400
