111
00:19:59.401 --> 00:19:59.800
I.

112
00:20:02.001 --> 00:20:10.300
I know that many of them are demoralized by the confusion and waste they confront in their work as a result of failed and failing policies.

113
00:20:11.501 --> 00:20:15.100
Our instructions to the groups we enlist will be simple and direct.

114
00:20:16.001 --> 00:20:26.600
We will remind them that government programs exist at the sufferance of the American taxpayer and are paid for with money earned by working men and women.

115
00:20:27.201 --> 00:20:37.100
And programs that represent a waste of their money, a theft from their pocketbooks, must have that waste eliminated or that program must go.

116
00:20:49.801 --> 00:20:55.800
It must go by executive order where possible, by congressional action where necessary.

117
00:20:56.601 --> 00:21:15.000
Everything that can be run more effectively by state and local government we shall turn over to State and local government, along along with the funding sources to pay for it.

118
00:21:15.601 --> 00:21:27.000
We're going to put an end to the money merry go round, where our money becomes Washington's money to be sent by States and cities exactly the way the federal bureaucrats tell us it has to be spent.

119
00:21:35.201 --> 00:21:46.500
I will not accept the excuse that the federal government has grown so big and powerful that it is beyond the control of any president, any administration or Congress.

120
00:21:46.801 --> 00:22:00.400
We are going to put an end to the notion that the American taxpayer exists to fund the federal government, the federal government, The federal government exists to serve the American people.

121
00:22:29.001 --> 00:22:33.800
On January 20th, we are going to re establish that truth.

122
00:22:34.401 --> 00:22:45.000
Also on that date, we are going to initiate action to get substantial relief for our taxpaying citizens and action to put people back to work.

123
00:22:52.801 --> 00:22:58.700
None of this, none of this will be based on any new form of monetary tinkering or fiscal sleight of hand.

124
00:22:59.401 --> 00:23:05.500
We will simply apply to government the common sense that we all use in our daily lives.

125
00:23:09.701 --> 00:23:14.100
Work, work and family are at the center of our lives.

126
00:23:14.101 --> 00:23:16.500
The foundation of our dignity is a free people.

127
00:23:17.201 --> 00:23:24.000
When we deprive people of what they've earned or take away their jobs, we destroy their dignity and undermine their families.

128
00:23:24.501 --> 00:23:34.300
We can't support families unless there are jobs, and we can't have jobs unless the people have both money to invest and the faith to invest it.

129
00:23:42.301 --> 00:23:59.600
These these are concepts that stem from an economic system that for more than 200 years has helped us master a continent, create a previously undreamed of prosperity for our people, and has fed millions of others around the globe.

130
00:24:00.001 --> 00:24:14.100
And that system will continue to serve us in the future if our government will stop ignoring the basic values on which it was built and stop betraying the trust and goodwill of the American workers who keep it were going.

131
00:24:26.201 --> 00:24:35.400
The American people are carrying the heaviest peacetime tax burden in our nation's history, and it will grow even heavier under present law next January.

132
00:24:36.101 --> 00:24:44.100
We're taxing ourselves into economic exhaustion and stagnation, crushing our ability and incentive to save, invest and produce.

133
00:24:44.701 --> 00:24:45.600
This must stop.

134
00:24:46.301 --> 00:24:50.900
We must halt this fiscal self destruction and restore sanity to our economic system.

135
00:24:51.601 --> 00:24:58.000
I've long advocated a 30% reduction in income tax rates over a period of three years.

136
00:24:58.701 --> 00:25:18.500
This phase tax reduction, this phase tax reduction would begin with a 10% down payment tax cut in 1981, which the Republicans in Congress and I have already proposed.

137
00:25:19.201 --> 00:25:26.400
A phased reduction of tax rates would go a long way toward easing the heavy burden on the American people.

138
00:25:26.701 --> 00:25:28.200
But we shouldn't stop there.

139
00:25:28.801 --> 00:25:38.400
Within the context of economic conditions and appropriate budget priorities during each fiscal year of my presidency, I would strive to go further.

140
00:25:38.901 --> 00:26:03.300
This would include improvement in business, depreciation, taxes so we can stimulate investment in order to get plants and equipment replaced, put more Americans back to work, and put our nation back on the road to being competitive in world commerce.

141
00:26:03.701 --> 00:26:09.100
We will also work to reduce the cost of government as a percentage of our gross national product.

142
00:26:17.701 --> 00:26:28.500
The first task of national leadership is to set realistic and honest priorities in our policies and our budget, and I pledge that my administration will do that.

143
00:26:29.201 --> 00:26:46.200
When I talk of tax cuts, I'm reminded that every major tax cut in this century has strengthened the economy, generated renewed productivity, and ended up yielding new revenues for the government by creating new investment, new jobs, and more commerce among our people.

144
00:26:47.401 --> 00:26:58.200
The present administration, the present administration has been forced by us Republicans to play follow the leader with regard to a tax cut.

145
00:26:58.801 --> 00:27:10.800
But in this election year, we must take with the proverbial grain of salt any tax cut proposed by those who have already given us the greatest single tax increase in our nation's history.

146
00:27:17.601 --> 00:27:21.000
When those when those in leadership give U.S.

147
00:27:21.001 --> 00:27:31.100
tax increases and tell us we must also do with less, have they thought about those who've always had less, especially the minorities?

148
00:27:31.701 --> 00:27:39.200
This is like telling them that just as they step on that first rung of the ladder of opportunity, the ladder is being pulled out from under them.

149
00:27:39.701 --> 00:27:56.300
That may be the Democratic leadership's message to the minorities, but it won't be our message ours.

150
00:27:57.001 --> 00:27:58.000
Ours will be.

151
00:27:58.001 --> 00:28:02.500
We have to move ahead, but we're not going to leave anyone behind.

152
00:28:09.301 --> 00:28:15.900
Thanks to the economic policies of the Democratic Party, millions of Americans find themselves out of work.

153
00:28:16.601 --> 00:28:23.500
Millions more have never even had a fair chance to learn new skills, hold a decent job, or secure for themselves and their families.

154
00:28:24.301 --> 00:28:27.600
A prosper a share in the prosperity of this nation.

155
00:28:28.301 --> 00:28:33.500
It's time to put America back to work, to make our cities and towns.

156
00:28:34.401 --> 00:28:45.700
Make our cities and towns resound with the confident voices of men and women of all races, nationalities and faiths, bringing home to their families a paycheck they can cash for honest money.

157
00:28:55.301 --> 00:28:59.600
For those without skills, we'll find a way to help them get new skills.

158
00:28:59.901 --> 00:29:06.300
For those without job opportunities, we'll stimulate new opportunities, particularly in the inner cities where they live.

159
00:29:07.101 --> 00:29:15.100
For those who've abandoned hope, we'll restore hope, and we'll welcome them into a great national crusade to make America great again.

160
00:29:22.901 --> 00:29:31.000
When we move from domestic affairs and cast our eyes abroad, we see an equally sorry chapter in the record of the present administration.

161
00:29:32.001 --> 00:29:36.900
A Soviet combat brigade trains in Cuba, just 90 miles from our shores.

162
00:29:37.701 --> 00:29:43.100
A Soviet army of invasion occupies Afghanistan, further threatening our vital interests in the Middle East.

163
00:29:43.701 --> 00:29:53.400
America's defense strength is at its lowest ebb in a generation, while the Soviet Union is vastly outspending us in both strategic and conventional arms.

164
00:29:54.101 --> 00:30:01.500
Our European allies, looking nervously at the growing menace from the East, turned to us for leadership and failed to find it.

165
00:30:02.301 --> 00:30:04.600
And incredibly, more than 50.

166
00:30:04.601 --> 00:30:19.400
As you've been told from this platform so eloquently already, more than fifty of our fellow Americans have been held captive for over 8 years, 8 months, by a dictatorial foreign power that holds us up to ridicule before the world.

167
00:30:20.101 --> 00:30:33.400
Adversaries large and small test our will and seek to confound our resolve, but we are given weakness when we need strength, vacillation when the times demand firmness.

168
00:30:34.001 --> 00:30:45.200
The Carter administration lives in a world of make believe every day drawing up a response to that day's problems, troubles, regardless of what happened yesterday and what will happen tomorrow.

169
00:30:45.801 --> 00:30:52.200
But you and I live in a real world where disasters are overtaking our nation without any real response from Washington.

170
00:30:52.901 --> 00:30:58.300
This is make believe, self deceit, and above all transparent hypocrisy.

171
00:30:58.901 --> 00:31:05.800
For example, Mr.

172
00:31:05.801 --> 00:31:07.300
Carter, Mr.

173
00:31:07.301 --> 00:31:19.300
